# Ural, Gafuriysky District, Republic of Bashkortostan

}}
Ural () is a rural locality (a village) in Yangiskainsky Selsoviet, Gafuriysky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 38 as of 2010. There is 1 street.
Geography
Ural is located  southwest of Krasnousolsky (the district's administrative centre) by road. Yangiskain is the nearest rural locality.
